==English==
===Transitive verb===
'''to root about''' (''past tense and past participle'' '''rooted about''')

# (''literally, of a pig'') To forage by poking the snout here and there.
# (''figuratively'') To rummage; to look for something in a somewhat aimless fashion.
#: ''I'm rooting about for ideas for a novel''

====Synonyms====
*(1): [[root around]]
*(2): [[root around]], [[rummage]]

===Usage note===

As with most phrases countaining ''around'' and ''about'', ''root around'' is more common in US usage and ''root about'' more common outside the US.